do walleye and smallmouth bass hit well in the summer and what lures work well for walleye because i'm going fishing for them in a few weeks yes on the weekend i caught smallmouth bass biggest was maybe lbs and walleye all in about hours including switching lakes the bass were slow but it was a cloudy day in a spot i've never fished walleye were hitting very nicely i find bass hit best on slow presentations this time of year actually i used the same jig for all those fish a chartreuse jighead with a white yum plastic grub never even busted out the worms i fished the bass with it in the afternoon and the walleye in the evening walleye are starting to go deep during the day but in the evening the bite can very ferocious in shallow areas close to weeds rocks and dropoffs my technique of the day was to slowly slowly drag the jig along the bottom that's it and somehow i never got snagged and caught fish without re tying my buddy caught bass with his crankbaits haha so in the end my woman wasn't mad that i got home so late because i brought tasty friends Angling Striped bass Fishing rod Fly fishing Smallmouth bass Bangladeshi cricket team in Sri Lanka in 2005-06 Chew Valley Lake Poker jargon Donovan Huron River (Michigan) Queen (band) USS Tunny (SS-282) International League USS Sea Devil (SS-400) Music genre Geology of the Grand Canyon area Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 2004 World Series Green Day WFAN (AM) Shaggy dog story Lake Erie Lake Nipissing MTV2 Ron and Fez Van Halen Indianapolis 500 Fishing Drill bit USS Seadragon (SS-194) Civil engineering and infrastructure repair in New Orleans after Hurricane Katrina Debra Marshall Great Lakes Animal Crossing Ragtime Naval mine Shark Rock and roll Zander Futurama (TV series - season 2) Oasis (band) 2000 Australian Grand Prix 2005 Atlantic hurricane season Boundary Waters Canoe Area Wilderness Glacier Daylight saving time Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March Cliff Richard 2004 Atlantic hurricane season Ice fish